README

Remap is an addon for the Orbiter Space Flight Simulator.

It defines additional key mappings for direct control of the thrusters
for the currently selected vessel.

The additional mappings need to be added to the keymap.cfg file located in
the Orbiter install directory. Following is the list of supported thrusters
with default key mappings. You can copy-paste these at the end of the
keymap.cfg file and customize them to your liking. Unused mappings can
simply be deleted.

RCSPitchUpDirect = NUMPAD2 SHIFT
RCSPitchDownDirect = NUMPAD8 SHIFT
RCSYawLeftDirect = NUMPAD1 SHIFT
RCSYawRightDirect = NUMPAD3 SHIFT
RCSBankLeftDirect = NUMPAD4 SHIFT
RCSBankRightDirect = NUMPAD6 SHIFT
RCSUpDirect = NUMPAD2 ALT
RCSDownDirect = NUMPAD8 ALT
RCSLeftDirect = NUMPAD1 ALT
RCSRightDirect = NUMPAD3 ALT
RCSForwardDirect = NUMPAD6 ALT
RCSBackDirect = NUMPAD9 ALT
LPRCSPitchUpDirect = NUMPAD2 SHIFT CTRL
LPRCSPitchDownDirect = NUMPAD8 SHIFT CTRL
LPRCSYawLeftDirect = NUMPAD1 SHIFT CTRL
LPRCSYawRightDirect = NUMPAD3 SHIFT CTRL
LPRCSBankLeftDirect = NUMPAD4 SHIFT CTRL
LPRCSBankRightDirect = NUMPAD6 SHIFT CTRL
LPRCSUpDirect = NUMPAD2 ALT CTRL
LPRCSDownDirect = NUMPAD8 ALT CTRL
LPRCSLeftDirect = NUMPAD1 ALT CTRL
LPRCSRightDirect = NUMPAD3 ALT CTRL
LPRCSForwardDirect = NUMPAD6 ALT CTRL
LPRCSBackDirect = NUMPAD9 ALT CTRL

INSTALL

1. Copy the Doc and the Modules directories into your Orbiter install.
2. Launch the Orbiter and enable the 'remap' addon.
3. Share and enjoy.

BUILD

1. Ensure WINDOWSSDK and ORBITER paths are set correctly in the makefile.
2. Run 'nmake all' to compile the addon.
3. Share and enjoy.

